<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1367299" src="https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/uniqlo-re-uniqlo-sustainability-program-news-01.jpg" alt="" width="1494" height="995" srcset="https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/uniqlo-re-uniqlo-sustainability-program-news-01.jpg 1494w, https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/uniqlo-re-uniqlo-sustainability-program-news-01-360x240.jpg 360w, https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/uniqlo-re-uniqlo-sustainability-program-news-01-768x511.jpg 768w, https://s3.ifanr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/uniqlo-re-uniqlo-sustainability-program-news-01-1024x682.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1494px) 100vw, 1494px" /></p>
<p>Hypebeast 消息，优衣库宣布推出可持续项目 Re.Uniqlo，以减少其全球碳足迹。据悉，优衣库将把从优衣库和 GU 获得的旧衣物用作新衣物的制造材料和燃料（仅限日本），或是将旧衣物捐献给有需要的人。</p>
<p>Re.Uniqlo 项目将于 11 月推出首个新品 —— 一件 100% 由回收材料制造的夹克。</p>
